# Tools scripts

Dev scripts live in `tools/`. Source `tools/go-env.sh` (or use a wrapper that does) before any `go`/`gomobile` work so GOPATH/GOCACHE/TMPDIR stay on `/Volumes/JohnDovey` — see `volume-storage.mdc`.

| Script | Purpose |
|--------|---------|
| `tools/go-env.sh` | Source before Go tooling; sets volume-scoped `GOPATH`/`GOCACHE`/`GOMODCACHE`/`TMPDIR` |
| `tools/gomobile-bind-android.sh` | Builds `core/mobile` + `core/media` → `android/app/libs/core.aar` |
| `tools/rebuild-and-install-android.sh` | Bind AAR, then `assembleDebug` + `installDebug` on a connected device |
| `tools/build-windows-server.sh` | Cross-compile `server/` to a Windows x86_64 `.exe` **with full audio** from this Mac |
| `tools/build-macos-server.sh` | Build `server/` for macOS **arm64 + amd64** (and a universal lipo) **with full audio** |

## Windows server cross-build

Use `./tools/build-windows-server.sh [output-path]` when a Windows desktop binary is needed.

- Default output: `/Volumes/JohnDovey/tmp/walkietalkie-server-windows-amd64.exe`
- Requires `mingw-w64` (`x86_64-w64-mingw32-gcc`); the script installs it via Homebrew if missing
- One-time cross-builds of opus/libogg/opusfile for mingw are cached under `/Volumes/JohnDovey/tmp/opus-mingw-build` (Homebrew's macOS `opus` cannot link a Windows binary)
- Uses `GOOS=windows GOARCH=amd64 CGO_ENABLED=1` with a static `pkg-config` wrapper so cgo picks up transitive libogg/libopus flags
- Not yet verified on real Windows hardware — treat as a Mac-side produce-and-hand-off artifact

Do not invent an alternate Windows build path (e.g. plain `GOOS=windows go build` without this script): that yields a no-audio or broken-audio binary because of the cgo/opus/mingw requirements above.

## macOS server build (both chipsets)

Use `./tools/build-macos-server.sh [output-dir]` to produce Apple Silicon and Intel binaries (default dir: `/Volumes/JohnDovey/tmp`):

- `walkietalkie-server-darwin-arm64`
- `walkietalkie-server-darwin-amd64`
- `walkietalkie-server-darwin-universal` (lipo of the two)

Per-arch static opus/libogg/opusfile builds are cached under `/Volumes/JohnDovey/tmp/opus-darwin-{arm64,amd64}-build` so cross-arch cgo does not depend on a second Homebrew prefix. Same `-a` + static `pkg-config` pattern as the Windows script.
